<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="366" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,793,1504]" pageId="1" pageNumber="366">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,829,856]" pageId="1" pageNumber="366">Description.</emphasis>
Species identification is based on 
<bibRefCitation author="Linnavuori, R." box="[735,946,829,855]" pageId="1" pageNumber="366" pagination="1 - 17" refId="ref7467" refString="Linnavuori, R. (1978) Studies on the family Cicadellidae (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha). 1. A revision of the Macropsinae of the Ethiopian Region. Acta Entomologica Fennica, 33, 1 - 17." type="journal article" year="1978">Linnavuori (1978)</bibRefCitation>
. Description is based only on female specimens, since males are absent in our material.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,793,1504]" pageId="1" pageNumber="366">
Head, pro-, and mesonotum brownish yellow with dense brown speckles; pronotum sometimes greenish (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1–22" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1804,1829]" captionTargetBox="[161,1422,173,1777]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1433,166,1785]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–22. 1–3—Macropsis simplex Jacobi, female (1—lateral view; 2—dorsal view; 3—face); 4–5—M. tincta Tisheсhkin sp. n., male (4—lateral view; 5—dorsal view); 6–12—M. tuberculata (Linnavuori), female (6–8—holotype, photos by Alyssa Seemann; 9–12—females from Ambo, Ethiopia; 6, 9—face and pronotum; 7, 10–11—lateral view; 8, 12—dorsal view); 13–15—M. viridofulgida Tisheсhkin sp. n., female (13—lateral view; 14—dorsal view; 15—face); 16–22—Macropsis hippodameia Linnavuori (16, 19—male, lateral view; 17, 21—same, face; 18, 20—same, dorsal view; 22—female, lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772389/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="366">Figs. 1–2</figureCitation>
). Face unmarked (
<figureCitation box="[401,468,937,963]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–22" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1804,1829]" captionTargetBox="[161,1422,173,1777]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1433,166,1785]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–22. 1–3—Macropsis simplex Jacobi, female (1—lateral view; 2—dorsal view; 3—face); 4–5—M. tincta Tisheсhkin sp. n., male (4—lateral view; 5—dorsal view); 6–12—M. tuberculata (Linnavuori), female (6–8—holotype, photos by Alyssa Seemann; 9–12—females from Ambo, Ethiopia; 6, 9—face and pronotum; 7, 10–11—lateral view; 8, 12—dorsal view); 13–15—M. viridofulgida Tisheсhkin sp. n., female (13—lateral view; 14—dorsal view; 15—face); 16–22—Macropsis hippodameia Linnavuori (16, 19—male, lateral view; 17, 21—same, face; 18, 20—same, dorsal view; 22—female, lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772389/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="366">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
), occasionally somewhat darkened in upper part, in one female with brown apical spot. Pronotum in dark coloured specimens with two brown spots on fore margin behind eyes, basal triangles of mesonotum usually partially marked with brown (
<figureCitation box="[639,706,1009,1035]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–22" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1804,1829]" captionTargetBox="[161,1422,173,1777]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1433,166,1785]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–22. 1–3—Macropsis simplex Jacobi, female (1—lateral view; 2—dorsal view; 3—face); 4–5—M. tincta Tisheсhkin sp. n., male (4—lateral view; 5—dorsal view); 6–12—M. tuberculata (Linnavuori), female (6–8—holotype, photos by Alyssa Seemann; 9–12—females from Ambo, Ethiopia; 6, 9—face and pronotum; 7, 10–11—lateral view; 8, 12—dorsal view); 13–15—M. viridofulgida Tisheсhkin sp. n., female (13—lateral view; 14—dorsal view; 15—face); 16–22—Macropsis hippodameia Linnavuori (16, 19—male, lateral view; 17, 21—same, face; 18, 20—same, dorsal view; 22—female, lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772389/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="366">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); in light coloured specimens these spots almost invisible (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1–22" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1804,1829]" captionTargetBox="[161,1422,173,1777]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1433,166,1785]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–22. 1–3—Macropsis simplex Jacobi, female (1—lateral view; 2—dorsal view; 3—face); 4–5—M. tincta Tisheсhkin sp. n., male (4—lateral view; 5—dorsal view); 6–12—M. tuberculata (Linnavuori), female (6–8—holotype, photos by Alyssa Seemann; 9–12—females from Ambo, Ethiopia; 6, 9—face and pronotum; 7, 10–11—lateral view; 8, 12—dorsal view); 13–15—M. viridofulgida Tisheсhkin sp. n., female (13—lateral view; 14—dorsal view; 15—face); 16–22—Macropsis hippodameia Linnavuori (16, 19—male, lateral view; 17, 21—same, face; 18, 20—same, dorsal view; 22—female, lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772389/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="366">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Proepimeron with brownish pattern. Forewing semi-transparent with dark brown speckles, partially brownish, especially, in apical half. Veins of the same colour as membrane, in apical part partially dark brown. Speckles mostly concentrated at wing base, in central part, in middle of costal margin, and in first three or four apical cells, so that in light-coloured specimens two indistinct light transverse bands visible on forewing (
<figureCitation box="[1085,1154,1153,1179]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–22" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1804,1829]" captionTargetBox="[161,1422,173,1777]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1433,166,1785]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–22. 1–3—Macropsis simplex Jacobi, female (1—lateral view; 2—dorsal view; 3—face); 4–5—M. tincta Tisheсhkin sp. n., male (4—lateral view; 5—dorsal view); 6–12—M. tuberculata (Linnavuori), female (6–8—holotype, photos by Alyssa Seemann; 9–12—females from Ambo, Ethiopia; 6, 9—face and pronotum; 7, 10–11—lateral view; 8, 12—dorsal view); 13–15—M. viridofulgida Tisheсhkin sp. n., female (13—lateral view; 14—dorsal view; 15—face); 16–22—Macropsis hippodameia Linnavuori (16, 19—male, lateral view; 17, 21—same, face; 18, 20—same, dorsal view; 22—female, lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772389/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="366">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,793,1504]" pageId="1" pageNumber="366">Apex of crown and anterior margin of pronotum sharply angular. Median keel on face, pro-, and mesonotum visible, but poorly developed.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,793,1504]" pageId="1" pageNumber="366">
2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[213,229,1260,1274]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="366">nd</superScript>
valvulae of ovipositor with 1–3 large preapical teeth (
<figureCitation box="[824,961,1261,1287]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–81" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1732,1757]" captionTargetBox="[258,1328,184,1711]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[256,1332,166,1712]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 41–81. 41–43—Macropsis simplex Jacobi; 44–48—M. tincta Tisheсhkin sp. n.; 49—M. chinai Metcalf; 50—M. kanongensis Evans; 51—M. capensis (Cogan); 52–55—M. tuberculata (Linnavuori); 56–58—M. turneri China; 59–62—M. viridofulgida Tisheсhkin sp. n.; 63–67— M. hippodameia Linnavuori; 68–70—M. minuscula Linnavuori; 71–72—M. bussaensis Linnavuori; 73–76—M. thargelia Linnavuori; 77–79—M. nigrosignata (Stål); 80–81—M. bitaeniata Linnavuori. 41–42, 55, 59–60—2nd valvulae of ovipositor; 43, 61–62—female 7th sternite; 44—male 2nd abdominal apodemes; 45, 49–51, 63–64, 68, 71, 73, 77, 80—penis, lateral view; 46—pygofer process, lateral view; 47—pygofer processes, back view; 48, 67, 70, 76, 79, 81—style; 52, 57—head, pro-, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 53, 56—forewing; 54, 58—female genital segments, ventral view; 65–66, 69, 72, 74–75, 78—style tip. 49–50, 63–81—after Linnavuori (1978), 51—after Theron (1970), 56–58—after China (1925)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772393/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="366">Figs. 41–42</figureCitation>
). Female 7 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1080,1093,1260,1274]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="366">th</superScript>
sternite rather short and broad, with wide shallow notch on hind margin (
<figureCitation box="[619,703,1297,1323]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–81" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1732,1757]" captionTargetBox="[258,1328,184,1711]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[256,1332,166,1712]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 41–81. 41–43—Macropsis simplex Jacobi; 44–48—M. tincta Tisheсhkin sp. n.; 49—M. chinai Metcalf; 50—M. kanongensis Evans; 51—M. capensis (Cogan); 52–55—M. tuberculata (Linnavuori); 56–58—M. turneri China; 59–62—M. viridofulgida Tisheсhkin sp. n.; 63–67— M. hippodameia Linnavuori; 68–70—M. minuscula Linnavuori; 71–72—M. bussaensis Linnavuori; 73–76—M. thargelia Linnavuori; 77–79—M. nigrosignata (Stål); 80–81—M. bitaeniata Linnavuori. 41–42, 55, 59–60—2nd valvulae of ovipositor; 43, 61–62—female 7th sternite; 44—male 2nd abdominal apodemes; 45, 49–51, 63–64, 68, 71, 73, 77, 80—penis, lateral view; 46—pygofer process, lateral view; 47—pygofer processes, back view; 48, 67, 70, 76, 79, 81—style; 52, 57—head, pro-, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 53, 56—forewing; 54, 58—female genital segments, ventral view; 65–66, 69, 72, 74–75, 78—style tip. 49–50, 63–81—after Linnavuori (1978), 51—after Theron (1970), 56–58—after China (1925)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772393/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="366">Fig. 43</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,793,1504]" box="[199,757,1333,1360]" pageId="1" pageNumber="366">
Body length (including tegmina): 
<specimenCount box="[580,601,1334,1360]" pageId="1" pageNumber="366" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
, 4.2–4.6 mm.
</paragraph>
