<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="366" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,793,1504]" pageId="1" pageNumber="366">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,304,1406,1432]" pageId="1" pageNumber="366">Remark.</emphasis>
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Linnavuori, R." box="[461,669,1405,1431]" pageId="1" pageNumber="366" pagination="1 - 17" refId="ref7467" refString="Linnavuori, R. (1978) Studies on the family Cicadellidae (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha). 1. A revision of the Macropsinae of the Ethiopian Region. Acta Entomologica Fennica, 33, 1 - 17." type="journal article" year="1978">Linnavuori (1978)</bibRefCitation>
, widespread in tropical Africa. Specimens from different regions differ in body size; females from our material are somewhat smaller, than the ones studied by 
<bibRefCitation author="Linnavuori, R." box="[1173,1383,1441,1467]" pageId="1" pageNumber="366" pagination="1 - 17" refId="ref7467" refString="Linnavuori, R. (1978) Studies on the family Cicadellidae (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha). 1. A revision of the Macropsinae of the Ethiopian Region. Acta Entomologica Fennica, 33, 1 - 17." type="journal article" year="1978">Linnavuori (1978)</bibRefCitation>
. It is possible that this taxon includes several closely related species.
</paragraph>
